When he come back from the war? Oh yes, when - we'd been out the night before discussing this, we'd - both got to get marri
ed. So I said, well don't say anything about me yet. Anyway they were all - home, it was Christmastime. And we were all round the ta - table having our tea. Herbert says - dad - I'm sorry I've to tell you this but I've got to get married. He says, well I'
m very proud that you're doing the right thing. Yes. I'm very - I'm proud of you being honest about it. He says, also there's someone else. Of course dad didn't look at me, he looked at Ern. And then it hit him. No. My God. 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Alice{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. He says, come in the front
, I want a word or two with you. Where's Ern? Oh he hadn't happened come in for tea, he come in after for me, ready go out. 'Course and he had him then.
